Package: ubuntu-game-launcher
Source: ubuntu-game-session
Version: 0.7
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Ken VanDine <ken.vandine@canonical.com>
Installed-Size: 17
Depends: ubuntu-game-session, gamemode, mangohud
Conflicts: ubuntu-game-desktop
Replaces: ubuntu-game-desktop
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Gaming launchers and helpers for the GNOME desktop
 Adds gaming enhancements to the regular Ubuntu GNOME desktop instead of
 shipping a separate compositor or session. Use GNOME for everything (Settings,
 network, audio, power, the app grid) and reach for gamescope only where it
 helps.
 .
 Provides:
  - GameMode (always-on CPU/GPU tuning while a game runs — a near-free win)
  - MangoHud (opt-in FPS / frametime / temperature overlay)
  - ubuntu-game-run: a composable wrapper that adds GameMode, and optionally
    MangoHud and nested gamescope, around any command. Use it as a Steam
    per-game launch-option prefix: "ubuntu-game-run -- %command%"
  - a "Steam (Gamescope)" application entry that launches the whole Steam
    client inside nested gamescope so every game inherits FSR upscaling,
    frame pacing, and the MangoHud overlay
 .
 For the maximum-framerate console experience (gamescope owning the display
 with no desktop compositor underneath) use the ubuntu-game-session kiosk,
 which this package depends on and which also installs the Steam snap.
